    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - POWER TAKE OFF: ROCKWELL REAR ENGINE MOUNTED -
        DISASSEMBLE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="10">
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the PTO output shaft inner and outer seals with a suitable puller.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the outer snap ring from the PTO output bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300303">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300303" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300303" filename="../figg13/G1300303.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Remove Outer Snap Ring From PTO Output Bore</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a suitable puller to remove the PTO shaft, spacer and bearing assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300304">Figure 4</hotlnk>and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300305">Figure 5</hotlnk>). Threaded end of the PTO shaft is 1.0"-20 UNEF.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300304" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300304" filename="../figg13/G1300304.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Remove PTO Shaft, Spacer and Bearing Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1300305" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300305" filename="../figg13/G1300305.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Remove PTO Shaft, Spacer and Bearing Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard the outer bearing tolerance ring and outer ring from the bearing bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300306">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300306" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300306" filename="../figg13/G1300306.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Remove and Discard Outer Bearing Tolerance Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the gear housing cover bolts. Insert five 3/8-24 bolts with 2 inches of thread
                minimum in the threaded holes provided. Remove the two plugs at the idler gear location and insert two
                5/16-24 bolts with 2 inches of thread minimum. Tighten in an alternating pattern to remove the gear case
                cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300307">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300307" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300307" filename="../figg13/G1300307.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Insert Five Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the PTO assembly open side down.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Protect the drive gear from falling when performing the next step.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mount the PTO housing in a press and remove the drive gear assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300308">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300308" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300308" filename="../figg13/G1300308.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Remove Drive Gear Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the PTO assembly open side up.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use suitable levers to remove the idler gear assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300309">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300309" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300309" filename="../figg13/G1300309.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Remove Idler Gear Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the PTO gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>When removing bearings from gear assemblies, protect the gears from dropping.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a bearing splitter and press to remove the bearings from the drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300310">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300310" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300310" filename="../figg13/G1300310.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Remove Bearings From Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a bearing splitter and press to remove the bearings from the idler gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the output shaft bearings from the shaft and housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300311">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300311" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300311" filename="../figg13/G1300311.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Remove Output Shaft Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard the outer rings and tolerance rings from all bearing bores (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300312">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1300312" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1300312" filename="../figg13/G1300312.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 12. Remove and Discard Outer Rings and Tolerance Rings</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
